summary: I had 36 hours to understand two ML papers, build marimo notebooks about them, and submit a walkthrough. Pair-programming with a coding agent compressed the paper-onboarding loop into an evening of asking, building, and poking. The artifacts we built, hero banners, interactive sliders, live training races, denoising galleries, taught me things the abstracts couldn't, and the novel extensions came from following my curiosity when the experiments contradicted my hunches. The agent typed; I drove. Curious how an agent can accelerate your paper-onboarding without taking the wheel?
